Sentencas: Cermet anodes composed of Ni and Dy2O3 have been applied as anode for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells.
Titulo: Electro-catalytic activity of Dy2O3 as a solid oxide fuel cell anode material

Sentencas: Although the oxide ion conductivity of Dy2O3 is negligible compared to that of doped ceria (DCO), Ni-Dy2O3 cermet anodes have displayed very high performance comparable to that of the commonly used Ni-SDC cermet anode.
Titulo: Electro-catalytic activity of Dy2O3 as a solid oxide fuel cell anode material

Sentencas: Temperature programmed reduction study suggests that the catalytic activity of the Ni-Dy2O3 cermet might be originated from the hydrogen adsorption ability on the Dy2O3 surface, promoting hydrogen spillover process, and consequently enhancing the electrochemical oxidation of the fuel.
Titulo: Electro-catalytic activity of Dy2O3 as a solid oxide fuel cell anode material

Sentencas: Further, the electrochemical catalytic activity of Au-based cermet anode confirms that hydrogen adsorption capability is as important as oxygen-ion conductivity for the ceramic component in a cermet anode.
Titulo: Electro-catalytic activity of Dy2O3 as a solid oxide fuel cell anode material
